      "passage": "In historiography, the 'Great Man' theory posits that history is largely explained by the impact of highly influential individuals. However, the Annales School, emerging in 20th-century France, vehemently opposed this framework. Instead, Annales historians emphasized the role of 'la longue dur\u00e9e' (the long term)\u2014focusing on slow-moving geographical, economic, and demographic forces over centuries. They argued that individual rulers are merely the crests of waves on a much deeper, more powerful ocean of systemic historical trends.",
